# App Router

## Routing

- Use route groups `(auth)`, `(dashboard)` for layout organization — not URL segments
- Colocate `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, and `not-found.tsx` with their routes
- Use `generateMetadata` for SEO on public pages

## Data Fetching

- Fetch in Server Components by default — call `queries.ts`, not Supabase directly in pages
- Do not fetch in `useEffect` when a Server Component can fetch on the server
- Wrap slow async UI in `<Suspense>` with meaningful fallbacks

## Caching & Revalidation

- After mutations, call `revalidatePath()` or `revalidateTag()` in the Server Action
- Tag fetches with `fetch(..., { next: { tags: ['events'] } })` when using external APIs
- Use `unstable_noStore()` / `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'` only when data must never be cached

## Route Handlers vs Server Actions

| Use | When |
|-----|------|
| Server Action | All app mutations (create, update, delete) |
| Route Handler (`app/api/`) | Webhooks, third-party callbacks, external integrations |

## Middleware

- `middleware.ts` handles auth redirects and session refresh only — no business logic
- Matcher should exclude static assets and `_next`

## Assets

- Use `next/image` for images, `next/link` for internal navigation
- Use `next/font` for custom fonts
